The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                A 43-year-old tuberculosis patient hanged himself in an abandoned toilet at Medical College and Hospital on Sunday. According to police, a wardboy saw Arshad Ali Mollah, who was admitted to the hospital on October 12, hanging from a shower pipe with a towel.     A 65-year-old man died of an unknown fever at Medical College and Hospital on Sunday. Madan Das, a resident of Jagadishpur in Howrah, was admitted to the hospital on Friday. His blood test report, which will be available on Monday, will confirm whether he died of a mosquito-borne disease. Sheikh Sahidul Siraj, a 14-year-old resident of Kidderpore, was admitted to a nursing home with dengue on Sunday. His condition was stated to be critical.    Bholanath Das, a 65-year-old resident of Bally, was crushed under the wheels of an oil tanker on GT Road around 10.45am on Sunday. The driver tried to speed away but was caught by local residents and police.    Subhas Bhowmik, 35, and his associates Siba Das, 28, and Gaurav Bhattacharya, 30, were arrested from a hideout on Delhi Road on Sunday. Bhowmik was wanted in several cases of murder and dacoity. According to police, Bhowmik is a close associate of extortionist Ramesh Mahata. Bhowmik was remanded in police custody for five days. Siba and Gaurav were sent to judicial custody for two days.    Arkapala Dutta, a 27-year-old homemaker, committed suicide on Saturday night by jumping in front of a Shantipur-bound local train at Khardah station. Police said she was a resident of Mudiali.    Kalyan Bhattacharya, a resident of Attapara, was arrested near Sinthee crossing on Saturday night for allegedly abusing and assaulting cops after the taxi he was travelling in was stopped for speeding.     Tanushree Ghosh, a high court lawyer, caught a man who was trying to snatch her gold chain at Tiljala on Sunday morning. The man was handed over to police.                                                                                                                                                              
